Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modelling text data using autoencoders. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper explores the suitability of different models for constructing deep autoencoders. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as autoencoders are a popular technique in AI for unsupervised learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as autoencoders are also used for image data. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as autoencoders are a type of neural network.
